sudo apt-get update

sudo apt install apt-transport-https curl -y

Install containered ( Docker-Engine- docker ) ====================

sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings

curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg

echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install containerd.io

Creating containered ======================

sudo mkdir -p /etc/containerd

sudo containerd config default | sudo tee /etc/containerd/config.toml

Edit /etc/containerd/config.toml =============

sudo nano /etc/containerd/config.toml  ( set SystemdCgroup = true )

sudo systemctl restart containerd

Install Kubernetes ===================

curl -s https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo apt-key add

sudo apt-add-repository "deb http://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main"

sudo apt install kubeadm kubelet kubectl kubernetes-cni -y

Disable swapp ========================

sudo swapoff -a

sudo modprobe br_netfilter

sudo nano /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward   (Edit entry in ip_forward file and change to 1)

Exexcute above all the commands in both master and slave machines 

Instialisoing the kubeadm ==============   ( Master machine )

sudo kubeadm init


If master is not ready the execute the below commands 

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flannel-io/flannel/v0.20.2/Documentation/kube-flannel.yml

Then In master enter 

kubeadm token create --print-join-command ( After getting the token paste that token in node or slave machine )







